The root cause is that `Microsoft.AspNetCore.OpenApi` 10.0 upgraded from **Microsoft.OpenApi v1.x** to **v2.x**, which has major breaking changes. Here are the four issues and their fixes:

---

### 1. `OpenApiString` removed → use `JsonNode`

All `OpenApiAny` types (`OpenApiString`, `OpenApiFloat`, etc.) are gone. Use `System.Text.Json.Nodes` instead:

```csharp
// OLD
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Any;
param.Schema.Example = new OpenApiString("1.0");

// NEW
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;
param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");
```

---

### 2. `schema.Nullable` removed → use `JsonSchemaType` flags

OpenAPI 3.1 uses type arrays instead of a `nullable` keyword. The `Type` property is now a `JsonSchemaType?` flags enum:

```csharp
// OLD
property.Value.Nullable = false;

// NEW
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models;
if (property.Value.Type.HasValue)
    property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null;
```

---

### 3. `Reference` property removed from models → use dedicated reference types

Instead of creating a model and setting `.Reference`, use `OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference`:

```csharp
// OLD
var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecurityScheme
{
    Reference = new OpenApiReference { Type = ReferenceType.SecurityScheme, Id = "oauth2" }
};

// NEW
var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference("oauth2");
```

---

### 4. `OpenApiSecurityRequirement` dictionary key/value types changed

The dictionary now maps `OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference → List<string>` (was `OpenApiSecurityScheme → IList<string>`):

```csharp
// OLD
operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
{
    new() { [oAuthScheme] = scopes }  // scopes was IList<string>
};

// NEW
operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
{
    new() { [oAuthScheme] = scopes.ToList() }  // must be List<string>
};
```

---

### Complete fixed code

```csharp
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models;
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models.References;

options.AddOperationTransformer((operation, context, ct) =>
{
    var param = operation.Parameters?.FirstOrDefault(p => p.Name == "api-version");
    if (param is not null)
    {
        param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");
    }

    operation.Responses ??= new();
    operation.Responses.TryAdd("401", new OpenApiResponse { Description = "Unauthorized" });

    var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference("oauth2");
    operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
    {
        new() { [oAuthScheme] = scopes.ToList() }
    };

    return Task.CompletedTask;
});

options.AddSchemaTransformer((schema, context, ct) =>
{
    if (schema.Properties is not null)
    {
        foreach (var property in schema.Properties)
        {
            if (schema.Required?.Contains(property.Key) != true
                && property.Value.Type.HasValue)
            {
                property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null;
            }
        }
    }
    return Task.CompletedTask;
});
```

> **Note:** Collections on OpenApi models are no longer initialized by default in v2, so null-check (`?.`) or null-coalesce (`??=`) before accessing them.
